Dear valued customers,

We’ve received multiple reports of individuals impersonating the MUJI recruitment team and sending direct messages to customers with unauthorized and unverified job offers.

These messages, often sent via Telegram, are part of phishing scams and are not affiliated with MUJI in any way. Scammers may request a money deposit for the job or provide false documents to appear legitimate. Please note that MUJI does not use Telegram for recruitment purposes, and we never ask for any money or deposits during our hiring process. We strongly advise all customers not to deposit any money to unauthorized strangers.

As a precautionary measure, please avoid clicking on any links from unfamiliar or suspicious messages claiming to be from MUJI. If you’re interested in joining our team, visit muji.com/my and click under the Career tab for more information.

If you receive any suspicious emails or messages claiming to be from MUJI Malaysia, please forward them to customerservice@muji.com.my for verification.

Be assured that we are actively addressing this issue to ensure the safety of our community.

#scammeralert #alert #phisingscam #fake #fakejob #joboffer
